========,2,Sites of Interest.
========,3,Museum of History in Granite.
A unique attraction just west of Winterhaven is the Museum of History in Granite.
The museum exhibits granite monuments made from Missouri Red Granite.
Each is 100' long.
Subjects include a Korean War Memorial, Quest for the Sky, The History of Arizona, The Wall for the Ages and the eight monument History of Humanity.
The History of the United States of America Dedication is on Washington's Birthday 2014.
The History of California is being edited.
Smaller monuments include the Felicity Stone (sm), a Rosetta Stone for the future located at the center of the History of Humanity monuments.
The Museum of History in Granite is a candidate as a World Heritage Site.
In 2016 this museum will dedicate a granite monument for the History of California.
